RACE.RACE_TEXT: KEENELAND RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 80000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: YOUALMOSTHADME brushed with an outer rival a few strides after the start, dueled for the lead two wide, assumed command leaving the three sixteenths pole, and drew off under moderate urging. BARAYE dueled for the lead inside of the eventual winner, but proved no match for that one at the three sixteenths pole, gave way while hanging on her left lead, yet lasted safely for place. KRICKLE chased two wide and between horses, then sustained stride along the rail through the lane to gain show at the sixteenth pole. LATE NITE MISTRESS brushed with an inner rival in the early stages, tracked four to three wide entering the turn, then lacked a bid while hanging on her left lead. AIM HIGHER raced forwardly along the inside before being taken in hand approaching the three furlong pole, got subtly shuffled back inside of a rival turning for home, and improved along the rail late. GLORIETTE sprinted for a furlong with the rider having his feet out of the irons following the post parade, pursued from midpack early on, checked lightly at the three furlong pole, took the turn in the three to four paths, shifted ground further out in upper stretch, and lacked a bid. SAPPHIRE NIGHTS pressed three wide early on, chased his inner pair of counterparts around the turn, and gave way. FOOLISH FRONT FIFI was off slow, trailed three wide, and moved up. PROGNOSTICATE broke a step slow, raced keenly while hustled between horses out of the gates, steadied out of tight quarters leaving the chute, fanned to the six path at the three furlong pole while far back, and made little impact. BINGO'S DREAM was outrun along the inside.

MAKE THE BOYS WINK saved ground while unhurried along the inside, and improved in upper stretch. MORETHANANYONE cleared off around the first turn, met a pair of outer bids entering the far turn, and weakened in upper stretch. MASTERFUL MEG steadied when pinched between horses early on, and failed to factor along the inside.
